summary: How many references to pop culture Cyberpunk-style movies and books will there be in CP2077? There has to be at least one...
body:
How many references to pop culture Cyberpunk-style movies and books will there be in CP2077? There has to be at least one Bladerunner. Maybe Judge Dredd? Deus Ex? Other movies I’m not familiar with?

Would be pretty cool, especially if they are planning on making most buildings have exploitable interiors (unlike Fallout 4 where most buildings are conveniently boarded up) means they can pack a lot of secrets in!!

summary:
I know everyone seems to be giving CP2077 crap for being in first person, but I’m actually all for it and am super excited! 
It...
body:
I know everyone seems to be giving CP2077 crap for being in first person, but I’m actually all for it and am super excited!

It also means that the graphics should run better because it only needs to render what’s in your eye-line, it doesn’t need to waste resources rendereing your whole surroundings.

summary: So since the devs said the player can’t get cyberpsychosis (losing your sense of self from getting too many cybernetics), the...
body: So since the devs said the player can’t get cyberpsychosis (losing your sense of self from getting too many cybernetics), the ‘humanity cost’ from buying the cybernetics is probably related to how others see you. Maybe techies, fixers, and robots will like you better when you’re more cybernetic, whereas ordinary people or maybe that religious order in the demo may react better to a more human V. That could open up different quest endings, too
